1
00:00:08,682 --> 00:00:11,982
-That does it! If he doesn't make it
back here in time,

2
00:00:11,982 --> 00:00:14,361
I'll never forgive that jerk!

3
00:00:14,361 --> 00:00:15,894
I'll blacklist him from my cafe,

4
00:00:15,927 --> 00:00:18,627
then I'll burn up
every figure in his collection!

5
00:00:18,661 --> 00:00:19,927
[ Laughs evilly ]

6
00:00:19,961 --> 00:00:23,327
-What's gotten into you?
You sound so evil.

7
00:00:23,361 --> 00:00:25,627
-You've shown yourself,
Darth Jiro.

8
00:00:25,661 --> 00:00:28,494
I wish you'd cool it
with that evil laugh, though.

9
00:00:28,527 --> 00:00:32,427
Believe me, I have enough
depressing company as it is.

10
00:00:32,461 --> 00:00:34,227
-S-Staz!

11
00:00:34,261 --> 00:00:35,527
W-What took you so long?!

12
00:00:35,561 --> 00:00:37,227
-Hmm. What's that stuff?

13
00:00:37,261 --> 00:00:40,427
-It's a magical-essence formula,
but this is the last one!

14
00:00:40,461 --> 00:00:42,227
[ Screams ]

15
00:00:42,261 --> 00:00:43,527
-Man, that hit the spot.

16
00:00:43,561 --> 00:00:45,394
-I can't believe
you just did that!

17
00:00:45,427 --> 00:00:46,994
What the hell
were you thinking?!

18
00:01:03,827 --> 00:01:07,827
-[ Singing in Japanese ]

19
00:02:24,795 --> 00:02:26,862
-Well, that's all Wolf's fault.

20
00:02:26,895 --> 00:02:28,728
-Are you kidding me?
It's all <i>your</i> fault!

21
00:02:28,762 --> 00:02:30,328
You're the reason
we're in this mess!

22
00:02:30,362 --> 00:02:32,095
-Come on -- he didn't tell me

23
00:02:32,128 --> 00:02:34,462
you guys were keeping
Fuyumi alive with that formula.

24
00:02:34,495 --> 00:02:36,328
Anybody would have done that,
right?

25
00:02:36,362 --> 00:02:37,595
-I think if it were me,

26
00:02:37,628 --> 00:02:39,295
I would've asked
if I could have a drink

27
00:02:39,328 --> 00:02:40,862
before just gulping it all down.

28
00:02:40,895 --> 00:02:43,695
-Is there some manner
of disagreement occurring here?

29
00:02:43,728 --> 00:02:45,362
-That's none of your business.

30
00:02:45,395 --> 00:02:47,862
Now go on and look
for some panties or something.

31
00:02:47,895 --> 00:02:50,262
-As the young lady and I
haven't met before,

32
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:51,762
without a proper introduction,

33
00:02:51,795 --> 00:02:54,262
she might actually <i>believe</i>
I'm that sort of person.

34
00:02:54,295 --> 00:02:56,195
Isn't that right, my dear?

35
00:02:56,228 --> 00:02:58,262
-I-It's so nice to meet you.

36
00:02:58,295 --> 00:03:00,262
-Call me "Braz."
I insist.

37
00:03:00,295 --> 00:03:02,495
And might I inquire
as to <i>your</i> name?

38
00:03:02,528 --> 00:03:03,762
-Uh, I'm Fuyumi.

39
00:03:03,795 --> 00:03:05,762
-What a beautiful name you have.

40
00:03:05,795 --> 00:03:08,262
My brother's told me
so much about you.

41
00:03:08,295 --> 00:03:11,128
I'm aware of your condition,
my sweet,

42
00:03:11,162 --> 00:03:13,728
and I can easily remedy it
for you.

43
00:03:13,762 --> 00:03:16,728
-Hey. Don't go overstepping
your bounds.

44
00:03:16,762 --> 00:03:19,428
-You did tell me
this was urgent, didn't you?

45
00:03:19,462 --> 00:03:20,795
-Stop trying to make it look

46
00:03:20,828 --> 00:03:23,162
like you're doing me
some gigantic favor.

47
00:03:23,195 --> 00:03:24,662
I can handle this all by myself.

48
00:03:24,695 --> 00:03:25,728
[ Snap! Crack! ]
[ Both gasp ]

49
00:03:25,762 --> 00:03:26,828
-Very well.

50
00:03:26,862 --> 00:03:29,195
Again, I <i>bend</i> to your will.

51
00:03:29,228 --> 00:03:31,528
How do you plan
to save this girl's life

52
00:03:31,562 --> 00:03:34,628
without the generous assistance
of your older brother?

53
00:03:34,662 --> 00:03:36,628
-Shut up, and I'll show you.

54
00:03:36,662 --> 00:03:38,328
[ Chomps ]

55
00:03:38,362 --> 00:03:41,395
I made a promise before
that I'd be her blood bank

56
00:03:41,428 --> 00:03:44,128
until the day
that I can bring her back.

57
00:03:44,162 --> 00:03:45,728
-What? Uh...

58
00:03:45,762 --> 00:03:47,162
Right here?

59
00:03:47,195 --> 00:03:48,828
-Yeah, that's right.
Now, hurry up.

60
00:03:48,862 --> 00:03:50,395
-But everybody's watching me.

61
00:03:50,428 --> 00:03:52,195
And if I drink that,
then I'll...

62
00:03:52,228 --> 00:03:54,128
-So you gonna drink this or not?

63
00:03:54,162 --> 00:03:55,462
Come on.

64
00:03:55,495 --> 00:03:57,528
-Okay. But at least
let me do it over there.

65
00:03:57,562 --> 00:03:59,395
-Just drink!
-Mmph!

66
00:04:00,762 --> 00:04:02,228
-How's that?

67
00:04:02,262 --> 00:04:04,195
More magic than last time,
isn't there?

68
00:04:05,462 --> 00:04:06,495
-[ Sighs ]

69
00:04:06,528 --> 00:04:08,362
[ Thinking ] <i>I can't resist.</i>

70
00:04:08,395 --> 00:04:12,628
<i>Staz, once I've tasted this,</i>
<i>I can't go back.</i>

71
00:04:12,662 --> 00:04:14,528
[ Sighs ]

72
00:04:14,562 --> 00:04:15,528
-[ Whimpers ]

73
00:04:15,562 --> 00:04:17,428
-I don't approve of this at all.

74
00:04:17,462 --> 00:04:18,828
She seems fine <i>now,</i>

75
00:04:18,862 --> 00:04:21,362
but who knows what could happen
if you continue?

76
00:04:21,395 --> 00:04:23,362
-Well, I don't plan
on keeping this up.

77
00:04:23,395 --> 00:04:25,228
She'll be turned human again
soon.

78
00:04:25,262 --> 00:04:27,195
Wasn't that the deal
we agreed on?

79
00:04:27,228 --> 00:04:28,795
-Indeed it was.

80
00:04:28,828 --> 00:04:31,428
Shall we go and have a look
at her original body, then?

81
00:04:31,462 --> 00:04:33,362
To East Demon World.

82
00:04:33,395 --> 00:04:38,328
Yes, back to your own territory,
where you and Fuyumi first met,

83
00:04:38,362 --> 00:04:40,828
and the place
where she lost her life.

84
00:04:40,862 --> 00:04:42,628
-Well, well.

85
00:04:42,662 --> 00:04:44,395
Looks like
another slow day, huh?

86
00:04:44,428 --> 00:04:45,428
[ Both gasp ]

87
00:04:45,462 --> 00:04:48,095
-Boss!
-Ugh! Is that me?

88
00:04:48,128 --> 00:04:49,762
-It's Yoshida!
Did you forget?!

89
00:04:49,795 --> 00:04:52,395
-Oh. Right.
So, what happened to <i>you,</i> Dek?

90
00:04:52,428 --> 00:04:54,828
-Uh, things have been
a little crazy here.

91
00:04:54,862 --> 00:04:58,162
-Don't you have any clothes
of your own, Tsuboi?

92
00:04:58,195 --> 00:05:00,528
-Uh, he's only doing it
'cause you told him to.

93
00:05:00,562 --> 00:05:01,828
-And my name is Yoshida, Sir.

94
00:05:01,862 --> 00:05:03,495
-[ Clears throat ]

95
00:05:03,528 --> 00:05:05,762
-Tell you what -- Let's not
worry about the details.

96
00:05:05,795 --> 00:05:07,595
Hey, Saty, grab me a beer.

97
00:05:07,628 --> 00:05:09,328
-Sounds good.

98
00:05:09,362 --> 00:05:10,328
Huh?

99
00:05:10,362 --> 00:05:11,328
Hey, who's the kid?

100
00:05:11,362 --> 00:05:13,228
She a new recruit?

101
00:05:13,262 --> 00:05:14,628
-Her? That's my sister.

102
00:05:14,662 --> 00:05:16,128
-Huh?

103
00:05:16,162 --> 00:05:18,628
-Honestly,
I can't conceal my disgust.

104
00:05:18,662 --> 00:05:20,595
To think you've actually chosen

105
00:05:20,628 --> 00:05:23,795
to spend your time
with these uncouth characters.

106
00:05:23,828 --> 00:05:25,595
[ Both shuddering ]

107
00:05:25,628 --> 00:05:28,695
-What -- Can't you go
to the restroom by yourself?

108
00:05:28,728 --> 00:05:30,595
-Something doesn't smell right.

109
00:05:30,628 --> 00:05:32,195
-Duh.
Look where we are.

110
00:05:32,228 --> 00:05:34,395
-Come on.
I'm trying to be serious.

111
00:05:34,428 --> 00:05:36,628
So, how much do you think
your brother really knows?

112
00:05:36,662 --> 00:05:38,328
-I'm not too sure.

113
00:05:38,362 --> 00:05:40,395
It's possible
he could know about <i>everything.</i>

114
00:05:40,428 --> 00:05:42,528
Or it could just be an act.

115
00:05:42,562 --> 00:05:44,428
But one thing I <i>do</i> know --

116
00:05:44,462 --> 00:05:47,228
My brother is
always up to something.

117
00:05:47,262 --> 00:05:51,228
-What is this thing?
Is it edible?

118
00:05:51,262 --> 00:05:53,162
-Trust me --
If he told you anything...

119
00:05:53,195 --> 00:05:54,428
-Aah!

120
00:05:54,462 --> 00:05:56,528
-...you can be positive
there's a catch.

121
00:05:56,562 --> 00:05:59,428
-He said something earlier
that's bugging me.

122
00:06:01,362 --> 00:06:03,395
-Now that Liz's job
is completed,

123
00:06:03,428 --> 00:06:05,528
I'd like to do
a little sightseeing

124
00:06:05,562 --> 00:06:07,295
down here in the demon world.

125
00:06:07,328 --> 00:06:09,795
-Oh. I see. Would you like me
to help you out?

126
00:06:09,828 --> 00:06:12,062
-There's no cause for alarm,
my dear.

127
00:06:12,095 --> 00:06:14,495
But I must say
I'm rather surprised.

128
00:06:14,528 --> 00:06:16,695
Why would a professional,
such as yourself,

129
00:06:16,728 --> 00:06:19,328
assist the others
in resurrecting that young lady?

130
00:06:19,362 --> 00:06:21,328
-Oh. Well, I just...

131
00:06:21,362 --> 00:06:23,662
-She must be
of great importance to you --

132
00:06:23,695 --> 00:06:26,728
perhaps even more than
the others could ever imagine.

133
00:06:26,762 --> 00:06:27,828
-Huh?

134
00:06:27,862 --> 00:06:29,595
-You sure looked pathetic
in there

135
00:06:29,628 --> 00:06:31,562
with all that sucking up
you were doing.

136
00:06:31,595 --> 00:06:33,762
-Hey! Shut up, all right?!
It's not like I had a choice!

137
00:06:33,795 --> 00:06:35,062
Anyway, that's not the point!

138
00:06:35,095 --> 00:06:36,428
-Well, if I were you,

139
00:06:36,462 --> 00:06:38,762
I wouldn't start worrying
about any of that stuff.

140
00:06:38,795 --> 00:06:40,428
I know from personal experience

141
00:06:40,462 --> 00:06:42,462
that if he suggests
you do something,

142
00:06:42,495 --> 00:06:44,628
it'll always benefit <i>him</i>
in the long run.

143
00:06:44,662 --> 00:06:46,395
-[ Sighs ]
Yeah, well, anyway,

144
00:06:46,428 --> 00:06:49,528
when Fuyumi wakes up,
give her this.

145
00:06:51,095 --> 00:06:52,428
-What is it?

146
00:06:52,462 --> 00:06:54,228
-It's a bell,
and if she rings it three times,

147
00:06:54,262 --> 00:06:55,695
then I'll come to her.

148
00:06:55,728 --> 00:06:58,162
Tell Fuyumi to call me
if anything happens, okay?

149
00:06:58,195 --> 00:06:59,262
Later!

150
00:06:59,295 --> 00:07:00,428
-Hey!

151
00:07:01,428 --> 00:07:03,562
[ Bell jingles ]

152
00:07:03,595 --> 00:07:07,162
Guess she doesn't come
when <i>I</i> ring it.

153
00:07:07,195 --> 00:07:09,562
Hmm.

154
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,062
-[ Sniffs ]

155
00:07:11,095 --> 00:07:13,562
-Sorry to keep you waiting,
boss.

156
00:07:13,595 --> 00:07:14,695
-That was fast.

157
00:07:14,728 --> 00:07:16,462
-We should be taking off.

158
00:07:16,495 --> 00:07:19,162
-Call us if you need anything!
-Sure.

159
00:07:19,195 --> 00:07:20,728
-All right,
let's have a look now.

160
00:07:20,762 --> 00:07:22,795
-Hey! Hold on!
What the hell's that thing?!

161
00:07:22,828 --> 00:07:24,828
-A little instrument
that I've developed.

162
00:07:24,862 --> 00:07:27,162
-Oh, great. And who are
you gonna torture with it?

163
00:07:27,195 --> 00:07:29,262
-There isn't anything
to be concerned about.

164
00:07:29,295 --> 00:07:31,462
-Come on!
Answer my question, damn it!

165
00:07:31,495 --> 00:07:33,828
-Her clothes are getting in
the way. Let's strip her down.

166
00:07:33,862 --> 00:07:36,062
-You must be out of
your sick, perverted mind!

167
00:07:36,095 --> 00:07:37,562
We can't do that!

168
00:07:37,595 --> 00:07:40,562
-I cannot understand why
you're getting so frustrated.

169
00:07:40,595 --> 00:07:43,295
You really believe
I'm that untrustworthy?

170
00:07:43,328 --> 00:07:45,162
-Well, pretty much, yeah.

171
00:07:45,195 --> 00:07:48,562
And if I see you try to pull any
crap pretending to save Fuyumi,

172
00:07:48,595 --> 00:07:51,128
then don't expect me
to ever forgive you.

173
00:07:54,395 --> 00:07:57,662
-All this instrument does
is take a sample of her magic.

174
00:07:57,695 --> 00:08:00,762
Resurrection is accomplished
by converting magic

175
00:08:00,795 --> 00:08:03,428
into what humans refer to
as the soul,

176
00:08:03,462 --> 00:08:07,062
then carefully placing it
into a newly replicated body.

177
00:08:07,095 --> 00:08:10,662
To carry this out,
I need to examine her essence.

178
00:08:10,695 --> 00:08:12,828
Do you understand now?

179
00:08:12,862 --> 00:08:14,462
-Fine. Do it.

180
00:08:14,495 --> 00:08:16,228
-Mm. Where...am I?

181
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:17,628
-Talk about perfect timing.

182
00:08:17,662 --> 00:08:19,062
Now lift up your arms.

183
00:08:19,095 --> 00:08:20,062
-Huh?

184
00:08:20,095 --> 00:08:22,328
-Ready, and...say "Ahh!"

185
00:08:22,362 --> 00:08:23,628
-[ Screams ]

186
00:08:23,662 --> 00:08:25,095
-Stop struggling!

187
00:08:25,128 --> 00:08:27,328
Hurry up
and get it over with, Braz!

188
00:08:27,362 --> 00:08:29,562
-Staz! What are you doing?!
-Stop whining!

189
00:08:29,595 --> 00:08:31,395
-Yeah, you shouldn't watch this.

190
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:34,328
The sight of what's about to
happen will scar you for life.

191
00:08:34,362 --> 00:08:36,328
[ Gun clicking ]

192
00:08:36,362 --> 00:08:37,762
-All done.

193
00:08:37,795 --> 00:08:39,728
-You sure didn't make it easy
for me, did you?

194
00:08:39,762 --> 00:08:43,328
Calm down. <i>He's</i> the one
that told me to do it.

195
00:08:43,362 --> 00:08:45,162
-Please, Staz.

196
00:08:45,195 --> 00:08:47,328
You're making it sound like
I'm that sort of person again.

197
00:08:47,362 --> 00:08:49,728
-Hey, if the shoe fits...

198
00:08:49,762 --> 00:08:54,195
-I'm going home to prepare
for her resurrection.

199
00:08:54,228 --> 00:08:57,095
Liz told me she'd quite enjoy
seeing more of this place.

200
00:08:57,128 --> 00:08:59,028
Would you mind
showing her around?

201
00:08:59,062 --> 00:09:00,728
-Yeah.
-Seriously?

202
00:09:00,762 --> 00:09:02,328
-Goodbye, Staz.

203
00:09:02,362 --> 00:09:05,462
-Wait. You didn't get
a clean sample before.

204
00:09:05,495 --> 00:09:07,595
Isn't <i>my</i> magic
mixed in with hers?

205
00:09:07,628 --> 00:09:08,662
-Relax.

206
00:09:08,695 --> 00:09:10,495
The task of removing your magic

207
00:09:10,528 --> 00:09:13,395
is, for me,
an extremely simple matter.

208
00:09:13,428 --> 00:09:16,262
You must continue to act
as her private blood bank

209
00:09:16,295 --> 00:09:19,395
until the day
I can bring her back to life.

210
00:09:19,428 --> 00:09:23,828
Promises are meant for keeping,
right, brother?

211
00:09:28,495 --> 00:09:30,795
And I assure you
my vow will be kept.

212
00:09:31,695 --> 00:09:32,595
-Aah!

213
00:09:35,262 --> 00:09:36,762
-Brother is so cool.

214
00:09:36,795 --> 00:09:39,628
-Think so?
He's carrying a man purse.

215
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:41,795
-Don't worry, Staz.

216
00:09:41,828 --> 00:09:44,162
I'll happily remove it for you.

217
00:09:44,195 --> 00:09:45,528
And then I'll possess

218
00:09:45,562 --> 00:09:48,628
a perfect sample
of your renewed vampire magic.

219
00:09:48,662 --> 00:09:49,628
[ Chuckles ]

220
00:09:49,662 --> 00:09:51,528
And I'll put it to good use.

221
00:09:51,562 --> 00:09:53,295
I promise you that.

222
00:09:53,328 --> 00:09:55,362
[ Laughs evilly ]

223
00:09:57,428 --> 00:09:58,695
-Aww.

224
00:09:58,728 --> 00:10:00,228
-Whatcha lookin' at?

225
00:10:00,262 --> 00:10:02,595
-Uh, n-n-nothing!
Nothing at all!

226
00:10:02,628 --> 00:10:04,495
-Really?

227
00:10:04,528 --> 00:10:06,295
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

228
00:10:06,328 --> 00:10:07,495
-Oh. Welcome back.

229
00:10:07,528 --> 00:10:09,128
-Uhh...

230
00:10:09,162 --> 00:10:11,462
So, how much they gonna pay you
to work here?

231
00:10:11,495 --> 00:10:13,662
-I felt kind of bad
just waiting around,

232
00:10:13,695 --> 00:10:15,162
so I decided to help out.

233
00:10:15,195 --> 00:10:16,395
Oh, look.

234
00:10:16,428 --> 00:10:18,162
You got such a cute one, Liz!

235
00:10:18,195 --> 00:10:19,362
-It's not that great.

236
00:10:19,395 --> 00:10:21,028
-Oh, is that right?

237
00:10:21,062 --> 00:10:23,395
Well, I'm glad you allowed me
to buy it for you.

238
00:10:23,428 --> 00:10:26,428
Hey, what are you guys eating?
Looks good.

239
00:10:26,462 --> 00:10:28,162
-You want to try some, boss?

240
00:10:28,195 --> 00:10:31,095
-Yeah, Fuyumi made us
a little human-world food.

241
00:10:31,128 --> 00:10:32,495
-Are you sure it's safe?

242
00:10:32,528 --> 00:10:34,128
I mean...

243
00:10:34,162 --> 00:10:36,095
-What kind of cook
do you take me for, anyway?

244
00:10:36,128 --> 00:10:38,395
I may not look it,
but when I was alive,

245
00:10:38,428 --> 00:10:40,195
I was in the kitchen every day.

246
00:10:40,228 --> 00:10:43,595
-Oh, yeah, I forgot --
You don't have a mom.

247
00:10:43,628 --> 00:10:46,395
I'll let Liz try it first.
Then I'll eat it.

248
00:10:46,428 --> 00:10:48,428
-Hey, come on!
That's not fair!

249
00:10:48,462 --> 00:10:50,562
My cooking's not that bad!

250
00:10:52,228 --> 00:10:54,762
-It looks...like a Tsuchinoko.

251
00:10:54,795 --> 00:10:57,095
-It's a Tsuchinoko omurice.

252
